description:
The Prawn in Hubble Palette (SHO), was a good target to test out my focuser backlash compensation. Worked pretty well and was able to consistently achieve the V curve throughout the imaging and refocusing process routine in SGP. Unfortunately limited clear skies opportunity and visibility only 2-3 hours a night before it disappears behind the house. After a couple of nights decided to see what I can pull out with my first attempt using PixInsight. Hope you like it!
17x 300” Ha
17x 300” Oiii
19x 300” Sii
Sharpstar CF80/500 + FF
HEQ5PRO
Zwo1600mm pro + EFW + 7nm filters
Zwo120mm mini + 130mm f4 mini guide scope
Pegasus Astro PPB
Pegasus Astro FC1
Acquisition via SGPRO, PHD2, Sharpcap PA
Calibrated with 20x darks, flats and bias each.
title: The flaming Prawn Nebula IC4628
